document_data.History:
The [[vampire]] [[archmage]] [[Manshoon]] summoned her to a meeting through a mind-controlled intermediary, [[Lothrae]] at some point in [[Mirtul 26]] or earlier that month of the {{yearlinkName|1479}}. There, he made a working proposition to her: that if she investigated the fugitive [[wizard]] [[Elminster Aumar]] for him and aided in the vampire's scheme to acquire ''[[blueflame item]]s'', he would richly reward her instead of revealing her activities. He also threatened her with his full fury if she were to expose him to the Crown.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|46-51|4}}

Not long prior to the Council of the Dragon, she'd slain at least one [[Sembian]] merchant by throwing a dagger into his eye.

Manshoon continued to make references to Talane's role afterwards;{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|95-96|9}}{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|130|12}} she ultimately appeared at the [[coinlass]] and thief [[Amarune Whitewave]]'s lodgings, sliding her blade under the window, while Amarune spoke with [[Ruthgul]], her mentor in thieving; Ruthgul was at the moment asking Amarune to fake some documents, and panicked at the sound of Talane's voice, revealing she'd hired him for it. After Ruthgul snuck out, Amarune received her; Talane revealed she knew of Amarune's origins, and attempted to impress her into becoming a "dirtyhands", a henchman, lest she reveal to the [[War Wizards]] that she was the daughter of [[Beltar Whitewave]]; she claimed she'd return four nights hence.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|138-140|13}}

Later, Manshoon resolved to use Talane to slay [[Gaskur]], a trusted servant of his patsy, the Lord [[Marlin Stormserpent]], in a bid to better manipulate him.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|271-272|26}} Talane slew Gaskur near Amarune's home, signing her work as Talane.

Lady Deleira Truesilver participated in the [[Council of the Dragon]].{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|144|15}} He sent her orders to find Amarune, and slay her after verifying whose body was Elminster's, through a mind-controlled, minuscule [[beholderkin]].{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|163-164|17}} She suited up in response.{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|167-168|17}}

She was later targetted by [[Targrael]].{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|227|24}} Though Talane seemed to have little effect, she actually served as Manshoon's host when the beholder he was directly puppeteering was destroyed, possibly being the means by which he saved himself.{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|233-234|25}} After the evening, she communicated with Manshoon through a drover in the back of [[Immaero Sraunter]]'s shop.{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|246|26}} The death kight followed her home, and there, delivered upon her a kiss, with a special ''enchanted'' gem in her mouth, whose mind magic allowed Targrael to invade Talane's; it was Targrael's expectation that the gem, sourced from Queen [[Alendue]]'s cache, captured minds, and she said Talane's death was easily achieved.{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|263|28}}
